node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Anxiety Healer on July 01, 2021 tagging @anxietyhealer, and @igototherapy. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'your therapist will: your therapist won't: @igototherapy hold space for you attempt to 'fix' you help you find the solutions you need tell you what to do guide you with reaching your goals judge, pressure, or shame you teach you new skills that you can apply to your everyday life just sit there and listen; it's an active process!'.

node.text:
🌊 Your therapist won’t fix you because you’re not broken; they’re there to guide you and help you unpack & unlearn the things you’re struggling with.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🌊 Therapy is also a place where you can learn new skills and figure out solutions that work for you - your therapist won’t tell you what to do.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🌊 Therapy is also not a place where you vent and your therapist listens; while that can happen, usually your therapist’s contributions are much more nuanced and proactive than just asking you things like ”and how does that make you feel?”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🌊 What else would you add?
